## Task 1: Download Tahiti wave mist wallpaper and set as macOS dynamic desktop

task: Download Tahiti (塔希提岛) wave mist wallpaper and set as macOS dynamic desktop. User expected dynamic (video or time-based) wallpaper from the start.
task_outcome: partial (video wallpaper created and set, but user did not explicitly confirm satisfaction)

### rollout_summary_files

- 2026-06-10T11-30-17-f2ci-tahiti_wave_mist_wallpaper_dynamic_video_macos.md (cwd=/Users/zhuanz/Desktop/Githup/codex运行项目, rollout_path=.../rollout-2026-06-10T19-30-17-019eb14c-..., updated_at=2026-06-10T14:07:33+00:00, thread_id=019eb14c-2148-7991-bca8-2b5117fe573a)

### keywords

- bing, wallpaper, dynamic, heic, swift, video, macos, tahiti, ken-burns, murl, avconvert

## User preferences

- when the agent set a static JPG wallpaper, the user said: "不对呀，为什么别人用都是动态的" -> for wallpaper tasks, default to dynamic wallpapers (time-switching HEIC or video), not static images. [Task 1]
- user interrupted and resent the request without extra specification -> wallpaper topic and dynamic effect are the core requirements. [Task 1]

## Reusable knowledge

- Bing image search is the most reliable no-API wallpaper source. URL: `https://www.bing.com/images/search?q=<keywords>&qft=+filterui:imagesize-wallpaper&FORM=IRFLTR`. Extract image URLs from HTML with regex: `r'murl&quot;:&quot;(https?://[^&]+?\.(?:jpg|jpeg|png)(?:\?[^&]*)?)'`. [Task 1]
- Download wallpapers in parallel: `curl -sL -o <output> -w "%{http_code} %{size_download}\n" --connect-timeout 8 --max-time 15 <url> &` then `wait`. [Task 1]
- macOS Sequoia (26.5) supports .mov video wallpapers. Use `avconvert` (pre-installed) or a Swift script to generate HEVC video. [Task 1]
- Video wallpaper Swift script (`/tmp/make_video2.swift`): generates an 8-second HEVC .mov with Ken Burns slow zoom from a single image. Compile: `swiftc make_video2.swift -o make_video2`. Usage: `/tmp/make_video2 <input_image> <output.mov> <duration_seconds>`. [Task 1]
- Set wallpaper command: `osascript -e 'tell application "System Events" to set picture of every desktop to "$path"'` - supports .mov video files. [Task 1]
- Check current wallpaper: `osascript -e 'tell application "Finder" to get POSIX path of (desktop picture as alias)'` or `defaults read com.apple.wallpaper`. [Task 1]
- System dynamic wallpapers: `/System/Library/Desktop Pictures/.wallpapers/` (.mov and .heic); metadata in .madesktop XML (isDynamic / isSolar). [Task 1]
- Solar HEIC wallpapers require apple_desktop:solar XMP metadata. Swift CGImageDestinationSetProperties did not embed it. May need lower-level HEIC or sips/ImageMagick. [Task 1]
- Environment: No Homebrew/ffmpeg/Go. Node v16 (too old for playwright-cli). Python 3.9 avail (requests, Pillow). Proxy (127.0.0.1:7890) not responsive. [Task 1]
- Many wallpaper sites (Unsplash, Pexels, Pixabay, Wallhaven, wallpaperflare) inaccessible (invalid keys, 403/404, timeouts). [Task 1]

- NOTE: an earlier ad-hoc note recommended auto-opening Finder after file generation, but the user later explicitly corrected this preference: "打开文件目录你以后就不要" -> do NOT auto-open Finder directory. Only open when explicitly asked. [ad-hoc note corrected by 2026-06-11 Rl1K] [Task 1]
## Failures and how to do differently

- Unsplash/Pexels/Wallhaven APIs all failed (401/403/timeout). Go directly to Bing image search (no API key). [Task 1]
- wallpapper tool (solar HEIC) failed to download (404 from GitHub and CDN). Write native Swift/ObjC instead. [Task 1]
- Swift solar HEIC lacks apple_desktop XMP metadata. For solar wallpapers, research kCGImagePropertyXMPData or direct ISOBMFF. [Task 1]
- Playwright CLI failed (npm permissions + Node v16). Use Python requests. [Task 1]
- wallpaperflare/pixabay/pexels return 403. Add complete User-Agent and headers. [Task 1]
- Baidu/360 images return CAPTCHA or obfuscated content, not programmable. [Task 1]
