task_outcome: partial (core files installed, some subdirectories not fully downloaded)

### rollout_summary_files

- 2026-06-10T11-28-00-5uJf-install_ppt_master_skill_from_github.md (cwd=/Users/zhuanz/Desktop/Githup/codex运行项目, rollout_path=/Users/zhuanz/.codex/sessions/2026/06/10/rollout-2026-06-10T19-28-00-019eb14a-0a47-7b73-a908-1d3751fc9a15.jsonl, updated_at=2026-06-10T12:06:29+00:00, thread_id=019eb14a-0a47-7b73-a908-1d3751fc9a15)

### keywords

- skill-installer, ppt-master, ultimate-ppt-master, github-raw, raw.githubusercontent.com, jsdelivr, codeload, github-api, network

## User preferences

- after installing a third-party skill, the user asked "我平时如何使用？" and "这个文件是不是下载到本地了？它占用了多大内存？" -> automatically provide: basic usage instructions (trigger words and workflow), file count, and total disk space. Do not wait for the user to ask. [Task 1]

## Reusable knowledge

- When GitHub HTTPS connection is slow or times out, raw.githubusercontent.com is typically accessible and provides fast per-file downloads. [Task 1]
- jsdelivr CDN (cdn.jsdelivr.net) returns 403 for GitHub repos exceeding 50MB ("Package size exceeded limit"). [Task 1]
- GitHub API zipball/tarball endpoints are slow on this machine and timeout on large downloads. [Task 1]
- Reliable fallback strategy for installing third-party GitHub repos: list file tree via GitHub Contents API (api.github.com/repos/.../contents), then download individual files via raw.githubusercontent.com in parallel with curl, setting timeout and retry. [Task 1]
- The ultimate-ppt-master-skill SKILL.md is at the repo root; trigger words include "做PPT", "做个PPT", "生成演示文稿" etc. [Task 1]
- The skill depends on Python 3.10+ and python-pptx >= 0.6.21. [Task 1]
- SKILL.md describes a strict serial workflow: mode selection -> strategy -> generation, with extensive quality and review steps. [Task 1]
- Installation target: ~/.codex/skills/PPT-master/ (107 files, 1.7MB after partial install). [Task 1]

## Failures and how to do differently

- skill-installer script relies on git clone, which times out on this machine. Before using skill-installer, test GitHub connectivity with curl -sI https://github.com and switch to raw.githubusercontent.com early. [Task 1]
- Python urllib parallel download without timeout/retry settings can hang. Use curl or requests with explicit timeout and retry. [Task 1]
- Before downloading subdirectories, check SKILL.md for script dependencies (e.g., pptx_to_svg, source_to_md) to avoid missing essential files. [Task 1]
- When reporting installation status to user, clearly state which missing modules may break what features and offer to complete later. [Task 1]

