## Task 1: Format account info to one-line file

task: Format account info from raw '----'-delimited string to a file. User corrected multi-line to single-line, and overwrite (not append) for single accounts.
task_outcome: success

### rollout_summary_files

- 2026-06-08T15-58-00-e2rW-account_info_format_one_line_overwrite_preference.md (cwd=/Users/zhuanz/Desktop/Githup/codex运行项目, rollout_path=.../rollout-2026-06-08T23-58-00-019ea7f4-86f3-75b2-a830-89053f9cd2dc.jsonl, updated_at=2026-06-09T00:57:58+00:00, thread_id=019ea7f4-86f3-75b2-a830-89053f9cd2dc)

### keywords

- account info, one-line, pipe delimiter, overwrite, format preference, 账号信息, 一行, 我就发了你一个

## User preferences

- when the agent created a multi-line file from raw `----`-delimited account string, the user corrected: "一行" (one line) -> default to one-line pipe-delimited format when processing similar raw strings; the multi-dash delimiter implies compact representation. [Task 1]
- when the agent appended a second account, the user said: "我就发了你一个" (I only sent you one) -> treat each new single-account input as a file replacement, not an accumulation. Only append if user says "加上" or "追加". [Task 1]

## Reusable knowledge

- Raw input pattern: `email----password----朋友xxx----工作xxx----父母xxx----birthday` [Task 1]
- User's preferred output format per account: `账号：{email} | 密码：{password} | 密保1（朋友）：{q1} | 密保2（工作）：{q2} | 密保3（父母）：{q3} | 生日：{birthday}` [Task 1]
- Use `cat > file << 'EOF'` (heredoc) to write/overwrite file with a single account line. [Task 1]
- When processing one raw `----`-delimited line, split into these 6 fields: email, password, friend_q, work_q, parents_q, birthday. [Task 1]

## Failures and how to do differently

- Do not default to multi-line format given raw `----` delimiter; the delimiter pattern itself suggests compact one-line representation. Default to one-line with pipe separators. [Task 1]
- Do not append when user sends a single account input. Single input implies file replacement. Only accumulate when user uses phrases like "加上" (add) or "追加" (append). [Task 1]

