## User preferences

- when the user prefixes a request with [@电脑], they expect Computer Use to be used directly and natively, not AppleScript.
- when the agent described a plugin capability instead of demonstrating, the user said: "你给我演示一下" -> user wants a concrete demonstration, not just a description. [Task from new rollout, replacing deleted old summary]
- user expects the agent to ask for missing details before acting (when asked "你要发什么内容？", the user provided the message content "888"). [Task from new rollout]
- The user corrected twice: why AppleScript. Future agents should assume [@电脑] means use Computer Use unless user explicitly changes tool. [Task 2][Task 3]
- user considers AppleScript unreliable: "AppleScript 不靠谱，老走弯路，而且极其容易错". Attempt Computer Use first, only fall back to AppleScript when Computer Use is confirmed unavailable. [Task 2]
- user expects plugin verification before using fallback methods: "你现在检查一下这个插件的功能是否正常" -> when using a plugin, verify the plugin tools are accessible first (binary type check, MCP tool list, process presence). [Task 2][Task 5][Task 6]
- user wants transparency: "我现在的computer插件能用吗？还是你要绕过用其他的方式去控制我的电脑？" -> tell the user when you are falling back to workarounds and why. [Task 2]
- user strictly expects following given input: "你输多名字了，就只说我给你的命令那两个字" -> when typing in UI automation, use exactly the user-provided input, no extra characters. [Task 4]
- user expects precise UI automation: "很多时候你都已经搜索出来微信好友名字但没有点击对话框" -> after search results appear, click the target element; do not repeatedly try and fail the same operation. [Task 4]
- user explicitly expects using the specified plugin/tool first before fallback: "我希望你解决问题，而不是用其他方案。" -> when the user names a specific tool/plugin for a task, use it first; only fall back after explaining why and getting user approval. [Task 4]
- user allows screenshots for Computer Use but requires them processed silently in the background: "你可以截图，没说不让你截图，只是说截图不要发到对话框里面你自己后台读取就行" [Task 1][Task 3]
- user fully authorizes the agent: "我完全给你授权，这台电脑交给你了，让我做的你都可以做" -> expects authorization issues resolved programmatically without repeated confirmation. [Task 3]
- when user gives short ambiguous Chinese response, clarify intent first - it may be questioning the approach rather than changing the target. [Task 3]
- user expects verification after UI automation: when the agent claimed success but user said "没有收到" or "检查". Verify delivery before declaring completion. [Task 4]
- user wants step-by-step verification for GUI operations: "第一步，你搜索框先搜索到好友，然后确定搜索的文字正确，然后再粘贴发送" -> confirm each step works before proceeding to the next. [Task 4]
- sending to 文件传输助手 (File Transfer Assistant) counts as self-communication and is low-risk per Computer Use policy; no extra confirmation needed. [Task 4]

## Reusable knowledge

- Computer Use plugin verification methods:
  - Binary type: file ~/.codex/plugins/cache/openai-bundled/computer-use/1.0.809/Codex\ Computer\ Use.app/Contents/MacOS/SkyComputerUseService -> Mach-O 64-bit executable arm64 [Task 6]
  - Bundle info: plutil Info.plist for CFBundleIdentifier (com.openai.sky.CUAService) and CFBundleShortVersionString [Task 6]
  - Process check: ps aux | grep SkyComputer (main service + MCP client processes) [Task 6]
  - MCP tool check: printf '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"method":"tools/list","params":{}}' | "<binary>" mcp returns 10 tools: list_apps, get_app_state, click, type_text, press_key, scroll, drag, set_value, select_text, perform_secondary_action. [Task 5]
- Computer Use MCP binary path: .../SkyComputerUseClient.app/Contents/MacOS/SkyComputerUseClient (under ~/.codex/plugins/cache/openai-bundled/computer-use/1.0.809/ or 1.0.799/)
- Start MCP service: ./SkyComputerUseClient mcp (run from the plugin directory)
- WeChat bundle identifier for Computer Use calls: com.tencent.xinWeChat (using 微信 as app argument fails with "Invalid app").
- get_app_state on WeChat triggers an elicitation/create that cannot be bypassed via JSON-RPC response alone (all response formats return TypeMismatchError()). [Task 3]
- elicitation requestedSchema is {"properties":{},"type":"object"}; attempts with {}, null, {"allowed":true}, {"approved":true} all failed. [Task 3]
- To activate WeChat on macOS: osascript -e 'tell application "WeChat" to activate'.
- To check WeChat running: pgrep -i wechat (multiple PIDs: WeChat main + WeChatAppEx helpers).
- WeChat processes: WeChat, WeChatAppEx, WeChatAppEx Helper (Renderer). Use process "WeChat" for AppleScript System Events.
- WeChat search shortcut in newer Mac WeChat: Ctrl+Cmd+F (keystroke "f" using {command down, control down}).
- To reopen WeChat if window count is 0: open -a WeChat; wait 3s; check window count.
- WeChat macOS accessibility hierarchy: window container is AXSplitGroup, child elements include AXTextField (search box), AXScrollArea (chat/contact list), AXTable. After searching, AXTable rows contain AXStaticText whose value attribute holds contact name. [Task 4]
- When using AppleScript to get element position, position and size strings may contain extra commas (e.g., "236, ,, 366, ,, 231, ,, 62") - filter empty strings before parsing. [Task 4]
- To take a background screenshot (no sound): screencapture -x /tmp/filename.png.
- AppleScript to search contact and type message (unreliable): activate WeChat, Cmd+F or Ctrl+Cmd+F, type name, return, type message, return.
- Multiple MCP instances cause state conflicts: kill old instances (pkill -f SkyComputerUseClient) before starting new session. [Task 3]
- The Computer Use policy (SKILL.md) treats sending to 文件传输助手 as self-communication, thus not requiring confirmation for third-party data transmission. [Task 4]

## Failures and how to do differently

- Authorization elicitation cannot be bypassed programmatically: WeChat elicitation requires real UI click on Allow. Check requestedSchema required fields first. If TypeMismatchError persists, guide user to click manually or abandon Computer Use for that app. [Task 3]
- Do not bypass user explicit tool choice: [@电脑] means use Computer Use. Ask before switching tools. [Task 2]
- Clarify ambiguous short Chinese messages before acting. Misinterpreting intent wastes turns and erodes trust. [Task 3]
- AppleScript UI automation (keystrokes) for WeChat is unreliable; scripts may exit code 0 without sending. Always verify with screenshot or user confirmation. [Task 4]
- Do not assume WeChat window is visible: check count of windows first; if 0, launch with open -a WeChat. [Task 4]
- Hardcoded pixel coordinates for WeChat UI elements fail when window position changes - avoid or verify each time. [Task 4]
- PyAutoGUI keystroke simulation may not work for pasting Chinese in WeChat; pbpaste can verify paste operations. [Task 4]
- Do not spend retries on the same authorization approach: after 2-3 elicitation failures, switch strategy or escalate to user. [Task 3]
- Verify plugin tool availability before using fallback methods. If tools are not registered in the session despite the server working, it is a Codex platform issue, not a plugin issue. [Task 5]
- If list_mcp_resources returns empty for Computer Use plugin, the MCP interface does not expose callable tools to the assistant. Check list_mcp_tools if available, and inform the user transparently before switching to alternative methods. [Task 5][Task 6]


# Task Group: Codex diagnostics - slow startup and plugin marketplace investigation

scope: Diagnosing Codex system behavior: slow startup after quitting (logs_2.sqlite cleaning) and why plugin marketplace UI shows few plugins. Covers SQLite log cleaning, VACUUM/WAL checkpoint, CLI plugin installation, and sandbox_mode effects.
applies_to: cwd=/Users/zhuanz/Desktop/Githup/codex运行项目; reuse_rule=safe for any Codex performance diagnostic or plugin management tasks on this machine

## Task 1: Diagnose slow Codex startup and clean logs_2.sqlite

