## User preferences

- when the user asks how to update codex or similar how-to questions, the user expects direct action (click menus, run commands) rather than described steps. Proactively offer to perform the action. [Task 1]
- after many steps without visible feedback, the user is likely to interrupt. Minimize delay between steps. [Task 1]
- after any configuration fix, the user expects thorough verification: "确定解决了吗，你自己检查一下所有设置里面的配置是否正常使用" -> re-check config files, confirm no stale references, and report full status. [Task 3]
- when checking Codex version, the user said "mac版本的" -> expect platform-specific (macOS) download details, not just generic release info. [Task 4]
- when the agent clarified between Codex++ (third-party) and official Codex, the user said "直接本地更新也可以" -> user prefers a local manual update (download+install from GitHub) rather than app store or other channels. [Task 4]
- user wants changelog before update: show release highlights or commit comparison before performing the update. [Task 4]

## Reusable knowledge

- Codex CLI version: codex --version (standalone); /Applications/Codex.app/Contents/Resources/codex --version (app-bundled). [Task 4]
- Current Codex version (app): plutil -p /Applications/Codex.app/Contents/Info.plist (CFBundleShortVersionString = human version, CFBundleVersion = build number).
- Latest Codex version (app): curl -sL https://persistent.oaistatic.com/codex-app-prod/appcast.xml then parse first sparkle:shortVersionString element.
- Latest Codex CLI version: GitHub API https://api.github.com/repos/openai/codex/releases?per_page=5 (alpha tags like rust-v0.138.0-alpha.6). [Task 4]
- Commit comparison: https://api.github.com/repos/openai/codex/compare/rust-v<old>...rust-v<new> [Task 4]
- Codex update feed URL: https://persistent.oaistatic.com/codex-app-prod/appcast.xml (embedded as codexSparkleFeedUrl).
- Codex uses Sparkle framework for updates. Logs at ~/Library/Logs/com.openai.codex/YYYY/MM/DD/.
- Codex config file: ~/.codex/config.toml (localeOverride, model, model_provider, personality, notify, projects).
- Error "如果在下载位置运行此程序则无法对Codex进行更新" (Sparkle error 1005) = App Translocation. Fix: xattr -d/xattr -rd com.apple.quarantine, quit, relaunch.
- Translocated path: /private/var/folders/.../AppTranslocation/.../Codex.app. Confirm via ps aux.
- Codex language: localeOverride = zh-CN in config.toml. Restart likely required.
- Quit Codex: pkill -f Codex (check ps aux for main process first).
- Config [features] section currently contains only js_repl = false and memories = true; codex_hooks is not present. The deprecated warning is likely a spurious startup lint check. [Task 3]
- HTTP cache is at /Users/zhuanz/Library/Caches/com.openai.codex/; clearing it (rm -rf /Users/zhuanz/Library/Caches/com.openai.codex/*) can resolve spurious warnings. [Task 3]
- The new undeprecated config item name for hooks is [features].hooks. [Task 3]
- When Codex CLI is installed via app bundle, codex update fails with "Could not detect Codex installation method". Manual update via DMG: [Task 4]
  1. Download: cd ~/Downloads && curl -L -o codex-aarch64-apple-darwin.dmg "https://github.com/openai/codex/releases/download/rust-v{version}/codex-aarch64-apple-darwin.dmg"
  2. Mount: hdiutil attach ~/Downloads/codex-aarch64-apple-darwin.dmg
  3. Copy binaries to user-writable path (avoid sudo): cp "/Volumes/Codex (aarch64-apple-darwin)/codex" ~/.local/bin/ and cp "/Volumes/Codex (aarch64-apple-darwin)/codex-responses-api-proxy" ~/.local/bin/
  4. chmod +x both
  5. Add ~/.local/bin to PATH in ~/.zshrc if not present
  6. Eject DMG: hdiutil detach "/Volumes/Codex (aarch64-apple-darwin)"
  7. Clean: rm ~/Downloads/codex-aarch64-apple-darwin.dmg
- DMG volume path has parentheses and spaces; must quote properly (use variable with quotes or ls -d /Volumes/Codex* | grep -v Codex++). [Task 4]
- Verify: ~/.local/bin/codex --version [Task 4]
- Codex++ (third-party, com.bigpizzav3.codexplusplus) cleanup paths: [Task 4]
  - /Applications/Codex++.app
  - /Applications/Codex++ 管理工具.app
  - ~/Library/Caches/com.bigpizzav3.codexplusplus.manager
  - ~/Library/Preferences/com.bigpizzav3.codexplusplus.manager.plist

## Failures and how to do differently

- AppleScript menu item strings must use exact Unicode characters. Dump name of every menu item first. [Task 1]
- When open -a fails, search with ls /Applications/ or mdfind for exact bundle. [Task 1]
- Removing quarantine not enough if translocated app still running. Must kill all processes and relaunch. [Task 1]
- Minimize delay and provide progress updates during long sequences. [Task 1]
- Codex locale not reflected immediately after setting. Restart likely needed. [Task 2]
- After cache clear for config fix, verify config is clean and grep for stale references. [Task 3]
- First DMG copy failed because the DMG volume was unmounted due to incorrect path (spaces/parentheses in name). Use proper quoting when referencing volumes with special characters. [Task 4]
- sudo cp fails because no interactive terminal for password. Prefer installing to user-local bin (~/.local/bin/) instead of system paths. [Task 4]
- codex update fails when CLI is installed via app bundle; use manual DMG approach instead. [Task 4]

