### Preference signals

- When the agent searched for "cxnexus" (typo) and found nothing, the user corrected: "是ccnexus" -> user expects exact project names. [Task 1]
- The user asked to see the project page and get a description before committing to installation. [Task 1]
- User asked: "如果不下载这个软件，现在的条件你能够有办法也能够做到吗？连接移动版。" -> they wanted a solution using existing tools (Python, Node) without downloading Go-based software. [Task 1]
- User specified upstream as "deepseekv4pro和flash" -> they have two providers to route between. [Task 1]

### Reusable knowledge

- ccNexus (lich0821/ccNexus) is an intelligent API gateway for Claude Code and Codex CLI providing endpoint rotation, format conversion, token pool management, and WebDAV sync. Latest release v5.3.0 includes darwin-arm64 binary. [Task 1]
- Environment lacks Go and Homebrew; Python 3.9.6 and Node 16.14.2 are available. [Task 1]
- System has proxy env vars: HTTPS_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:7890, ALL_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:7890. These interfere with local and tunnel connectivity. [Task 1]
- To bypass proxy for local testing: use --noproxy '*' or unset the vars. [Task 1]
- Port 3000 was occupied by a prior process (ccx-darwin). Use lsof -i :PORT to check availability. [Task 1]
- Python proxy script can do model-based routing: if model contains "flash" route to Gemini, otherwise to DeepSeek. Includes OpenAI-to-Gemini format conversion. [Task 1]
- localtunnel works but may fail when system proxy is set. [Task 1]
- cloudflared download from GitHub failed with 504; check curl output rather than assuming binary. [Task 1]

### Failures and how to do differently

- Proxy env vars break direct curl to localhost. Always use --noproxy '*' or unset them before testing. [Task 1]
- Port 3000 was already occupied; use lsof -i :PORT to check first. [Task 1]
- localtunnel may fail when system proxy is configured; try alternate tunnel methods. [Task 1]
- When downloading binaries with curl, check the output (HTML error vs binary). [Task 1]

