### keywords

- screenshots, images, no-images, token-limits, invalid_request_error, background-only, chat-policy, computer-use

## User preferences

- when the agent displayed screenshots in chat, the user said: "你不要截图啊" and later consolidated: "你可以截图，没说不让你截图，只是说截图不要发到对话框里面你自己后台读取就行" -> screenshots are allowed for Computer Use / browser automation but MUST be processed silently in the background and never displayed in the conversation. [Task 1]
- this is a hard constraint established across 5+ sessions (Jun 5-7 2026). Takes precedence over any skill, plugin, or default behavior that would produce images. [Task 1]
- the practical reason: rendering images in conversation consumes massive token counts, quickly exceeding the context window limit (1048565 tokens) and causing `invalid_request_error`. This is a functional necessity, not just a preference. [Task 1]
